        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <head>44. Memorandum for the Record<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d44fn0">Source:
                        Eisenhower Library, Project Clean Up, Intelligence Matters. No
                        classification marking. Prepared by <persName corresp="#p_GBGAJ1"
                            >Goodpaster</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1958-04-24">April 24, 1958</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On 24 April, at the President’s direction, I advised Gen. <persName
                        corresp="#p_TGNF1">Twining</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen
                        Dulles</persName> that there are to be no reconnaissance flights, by
                    military or other aircraft, over the territory of the <gloss target="#t_USSR1"
                        >USSR</gloss> or other Communist countries.<note n="1" xml:id="d44fn1">In
                        another memorandum for the record, dated April 24, <persName
                            corresp="#p_GBGAJ1">Goodpaster</persName> wrote: “A.D. asked if OK to
                        send a man in by low-flying a/c. After checking I told him OK.” (<hi
                            rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">G.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
